<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id05951365-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s2014"><num value="2014">§ 2014.</num><heading> Termination of proclamations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The President is authorized at any time to terminate, in whole or in part, any proclamation issued pursuant to section 2011 or 2012 of this title.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id05951366-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/283/tII/s204">Pub. L. 89–283, title II, § 204</ref>, <date date="1965-10-21">Oct. 21, 1965</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/79/1018">79 Stat. 1018</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
